**Hours:** Fulltime, 40 hours

**Location:** Rotterdam, The Netherlands



**\#block\-4 h1, \#block\-4 h2, \#block\-4 h3 { color:** \#000; } @media only screen and (max\-width: 767px) { \#block\-4 { padding\-top: 150px !important; padding\-bottom: 25px !important; } }

The Position



As a Commercial Analytics Intern, you will receive one core analytical project with a clear business objective and deliverable (approximately 80% of your time). The remaining time of your internship is dedicated to gaining structured desk exposure, providing hands\-on experience across different products and desks. You will also have the opportunity to work with commercial teams and learn how analytical insights translate into trading decisions and opportunities. Throughout the internship, you will gain exposure to physical, futures, and OTC markets.



In this role, you will work closely with the Trading, Risk Management and Commercial teams to support trading desks with market analysis, risk reporting, and analytics. You will be responsible for real analytical tasks used in day\-to\-day trading decisions.



(This is not a general business or administrative internship).



**\#block\-5 h1, \#block\-5 h2, \#block\-5 h3 { color:** \#ede6e1; } @media only screen and (max\-width: 767px) { \#block\-5 { padding\-top: 25px !important; padding\-bottom: 25px !important; } }

**@media only screen and (max\-width:** 767px) { \#block\-6 { padding\-top: 25px !important; padding\-bottom: 25px !important; } }

Your Key Responsibilities



Analyse price movements, spreads, and forward curves;



Support daily exposure and risk monitoring for trading desks;



Assist with scenario and sensitivity analysis on trading positions;



Help analyse PnL drives and market performance;



Maintain and improve desk\-level dashboards and reports;



Automate recurring reports using Excel and/or Python;



Work with market and position data from internal systems.



**@media only screen and (max\-width:** 767px) { \#block\-7 { padding\-top: 100px !important; padding\-bottom: 50px !important; } }

Your Profile



You are a recent Bachelor graduate in Economics, Finance, Mathematics, Engineering, Physics, Data Science or similar;



Has strong analytical and numerical skills and is comfortable working with data and drawing conclusions;



Has advanced Excel skills (VBA) and experience with Python, R, SQL or similar programming;



Has genuine interest in markets, trading, and commodities;



Preferably has prior exposure to financial markets or commodities;



Preferably has experience with data analysis projects or coursework;



**Proactive mindset:** you take ownership of tasks, ask questions and seek opportunities to add value;



**Adaptability:** a dynamic work environment is where you thrive in;



**Curiosity and learning agility:** you are eager to explore markets, products and trading str

**Working at CLUSE**  

Do you want to be part of one of the most exciting watch and lifestyle brands in Europe? CLUSE started in the Netherlands in 2013 and is now active in more than 20 countries with over 2,000 points of sale worldwide. We are a young and dynamic company (average age of 30\) with an enthusiastic, international team. Our culture is open and informal and since we have more than 10 different nationalities, English is our go\-to language!

 **Requirements**  

Our IT team is looking for an IT Support Intern. As part of the Service Desk, you will be the first point of contact for colleagues with IT\-related issues and requests, supporting the IT department in resolving incidents quickly and structurally.


Beyond day\-to\-day support, you will learn the inner workings of a modern IT department: infrastructure, cybersecurity, hardware lifecycle management, SaaS administration, and business applications. You will get hands\-on exposure to the systems that power an international e\-commerce brand, including our ERP (Oracle Netsuite), Shopify Plus and the Microsoft 365 ecosystem.


This role, potentially alongside your studies, offers real potential for growth and the possibility to take on larger roles within CLUSE.

**What you will do**

* Provide first\-line support for incidents and requests;
* Install, configure, and maintain hardware (laptops, peripherals, meeting\-room equipment) and software;
* Assist with on\- and offboarding of employees: ICT equipment, accounts and authorizations;
* Create and maintain user guides and internal documentation;
* Identify, analyse, and follow up on problems; manage incidents through to resolution;
* Monitor our cloud solutions and integrations to ensure maximum uptime;
* Support small IT projects, such as roll\-outs of new tools or process improvements.

 **What you will learn**

* Service Desk operations and structured incident management;
* Administration of a modern SaaS stack (Microsoft 365, identity \& access management);
* The fundamentals of cybersecurity in a real business environment;
* How IT supports e\-commerce operations, logistics, and finance in an international company.

**What we are looking for**

* Logical thinker with a passion for information technology;
* Eager to learn;
* Flexible, service\-minded, and with a hands\-on mentality;
* Strong communication skills in English;
* Available 5 days a week, of which at least 3 days in our Amsterdam office.



**Benefits**  

* 500,\- euros gross a month internship compensation;
* 1 day off per month based on 40\-hours per week;
* Employee discount on our own products;
* A CLUSE product of your choice as a welcome gift;
* Company laptop;
* An inspiring office @ Houthavens, Amsterdam;
* Flexible work\-from\-home policy
* Regular social events you definitely want to attend, organized by our Social Events Team.

**Curious to find out more?**  

Apply now! We would love to tell you more about this role, our team and the story behind C

Come reimagine hospitality with us as our new superhost of our Eindhovenlocation!


**Your mission should you choose to accept it…**



As our Front Office Intern, you'll be operating in all of our front of house areas, making sure that each guest is having the best possible TSH\-experience. Whether you're providing a flawless welcome and check in, awesome service in our restaurant and bars or just having a chat to make their stay truly unforgettable ― you are at the forefront of our guest facing operation. You know everything about our products and how to (cross\-)sell these to our guests. And it's because of you that everyone who enters our Eindhoven\-location will become a raving fan of TSH instantly!


**In case you don't know who we are:**



Known for being the rule breakers in hospitality, TSH is a fun, creative and inspiring environment where everyone can work, stay, learn and play and most importantly – be themselves. As an employer we look, act and think like a hotel, but instead we offer a lot more. Think student accommodation, long and short stay options, gyms, talks, events, rooftop bar and eat \& drink escapes as well as community and coworking spaces. Located in The Netherlands, Germany, Austria, Italy, France and Spain with several new openings on the way, this hybrid hospitality concept may take root in the heart of Europe, but our plans are set for going global.


**What You'll Do**


* You make sure everyone gets a warm welcome as soon as they walk in;
* You'll help our guests at our reception desk.
* You'll be a secret concierge to the city, answering all of your guests' questions about the best places to visit, eat, shop or party;
* Tidy home's a happy home. You'll make sure everything is spick and span in all areas and ready for the following shift;
* You'll help our guests with any requests or demands regarding our facilities (you may even pick up some new tech skills along the way!).


**Who You Are**


* You're currently enrolled in a University;
* Currently studying a relevant bachelor's in Hospitality, Sales, Advertising, Marketing, or Business;
* Enjoy receiving and taking responsibility and you can work independently;
* You have a flexible, hands\-on, motivated and positive approach;
* You're an octopus that loves to get your dexterity skills into action;
* You love responsibility and handle stressful peak periods like a pro;
* Fluent in English and Dutch – Know any other languages? The more the merrier!
* Hard working, responsible and a "let's do this!" mentality;
* You must be studying within the EU.


**What We Offer**


* An amazing work environment with a fantastic vibe and lots of positive energy.
* On the job coaching and guidance.
* Monthly compensation for your internship.
* The opportunity to work and learn at a dynamic, young, international organisation; we're a real game changer in the hospitality industry.
* A first glimpse into the world of Hospitality with one of the most innovative players in the marke
